Melania Trump, the first lady of the United States, and Jim Carroll, the primary drug adviser to the president, have reaffirmed their commitment to ensuring that the American people and youth can live in drug-free communities. In partnership with the Office of National Drug Control Policy (ONDCP) and the first lady's Be Best campaign, they aim to prevent youth substance abuse and raise awareness about the consequences of illicit drug use. Their focus is on primary prevention, which involves educating individuals about the risks of drug use and stopping drugs from entering communities. For more information, read the full article on Fox News.